>Lun 23 mars 2026, =C3=A0 19:44, Bernard Bel a =C3=A9crit=E2=80=AF:
>>https://roomi-fields.com/en/articles/b3-derivation-rules/
>>
>>Dans les r=C3=A8gles de d=C3=A9rivation que tu as document=C3=A9es, je vo=
is quelques=20
>>probl=C3=A8mes :
>>
>>1) Le mode LIN n=E2=80=99a rien =C3=A0 voir avec une d=C3=A9rivation cycl=
ique.=20
>>D=C3=A9finition (selon BP3 help) :
>>A "subgrammar" using (context-sensitive) leftmost derivation in=20
>>"production", and (context-sensitive) rightmost derivation in=20
>>analysis.
>>
>>En fait, tout est d=C3=A9crit dans :
>>https://bolprocessor.org/misc/docs/
>>(voir la page =E2=80=9CBP2 grammars=E2=80=9D)
>>-- "RND" mode: rules are applied in a random order. (Default mode)
>>-- "LIN" mode: candidate rule chosen randomly among rules yielding a=20
>>leftmost derivation.
>>-- "ORD" mode: candidate rules are applied in the order in which they=20
>>appear in the grammar.
>>-- "SUB" mode: same as "RND", but all occurrences of the selected=20
>>rule's left argument in the work string are rewritten simultaneously.=20
>>In this mode, for instance, p-substitutions and other kinds of=20
>>automatic (infinite) sequences may be generated. These derivations=20
>>stop either when a predefined buffer length has been reached, or the=20
>>weights of all candidate rules are null as the result of having been=20
>>dynamically decremented during computation.
>>-- "SUB1" mode: same as "SUB", but only one rewriting of variables=20
>>will be allowed. This mode is much faster than "SUB" and may be used=20
>>when it is certain that the first substitution yields only terminal=20
>>symbols.
>>
>>2) Je ne comprends pas pourquoi tu as chang=C3=A9 la notation, ex.=20
>>=E2=80=9C-mo.LIN=E2=80=9D au lieu de =E2=80=9CLIN=E2=80=9D
>>
>>3) Les exemples empruntant le vocabulaire du tabla sont mal choisis,=20
>>et musicalement incorrects pour la plupart. Il vaudrait mieux utiliser=20
>>un alphabet =E2=80=9Cneutre=E2=80=9D de terminaux comme a, b, c=E2=80=A6
>>
